column19: YES  This is a Mk1 Mazda MX5 rebodied with the MX250 body kit by Tribute Automotive of Dorset. New deep dish wire wheels and the paint job / stickering to create an authentic looking replica / homage to the Ecurie Francorchamps 1964 Tour de France winning Ferrari GTO 250. Title: Mr
column19: YES   This is an ex military 110 Defender FFR Tithonus. In 2000 the vehicle was subject to the Army Life Extension Programme - the following work was carried out; Rear and front heavy duty Wolf roll cage fitted hard top replaced with Wolf tall fibreglass removable top chassis outriggers reinforced rear cross member replaced standard military shock absorbers replaced with heavy duty 2inch lifted Wolf units track rod ends and radius arm bushes replaced rear and front seats replaced with Exmoor trim outlast heavy duty trim seats side rear seat belts x 4 fitted brake pipes flexi and solid replaced brake cylinders discs and drums replaced chassis and bulkhead wax injected. In 2010 the engine was replaced with a re manufactured engine fitted under military contract. The following work has been carried out since purchasing the vehicle; Landrover 16 inch Boost alloys fitted all round with BFG KM2 MT 255/85 R16 tyres fitted - with wheel locking nut kit. All lights replaced with LED kit and upgraded light wiring loom. Front military bumper replaced with Uproar steel bumper and end caps with fitted DLR lights. Front light surrounds fitted with grill protectors. Steel Side heavy duty tube protectors with side steps fitted. Rear NATO tow hook removed and replaced with standard tow bracket and adjustable tow ball. NATO light switch replaced with standard light control switch. Sound deadening mars fitted to bulkhead floor pan roof and side panels and bonnet. Interior of roof lined with additional sound deadening black material. Main body of vehicle resprayed in NATO green - roof side steps wheel arches front bumper light surrounds grills door hinges and all chequer plate sprayed in Raptor black.
